<p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">Published June 15, 2026 · 5 min read</p>

<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">The -OUS suffix creates adjectives from nouns and verbs (joy→joyous, danger→dangerous) and is one of Scrabble's sneakiest scoring tools. While the suffix tiles themselves are low-value (O1+U1+S1 = 3 points), -OUS words typically have power-tile roots that push totals well above 20 points. This advanced guide focuses on maximizing -OUS for competitive play.</p>

<p>Advanced players recognize -OUS as a bridge between high-value consonants and the board. The suffix uses vowels that might otherwise clog your rack, converting them into scoring plays.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Why -OUS Matters in Advanced Play</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
